RIDOCs Covid-19 update
04/23/2020

Todays stats continue to show an upward trend, demonstrating that we are not yet over the curve.

...

There were 8 more Covid-19 related deaths in RI, bringing our total to 189.
There are 412 new cases of Covid-19 in RI, bringing our total to 6256.
There are currently 267 people hospitalized in RI with Covid-19 illness.

RIDOC Transparency report:
As of today, there are a total of seven RIDOC staff who have tested positive for COVID19, and zero housed sentenced inmate. (One positive new commitment continues to be in medical isolation.)

Womens Facility:
As we mentioned in yesterdays update, all staff and inmates from the Womens facility underwent Covid-19 surveillance testing. So far there were two positive test results: one Correctional Officer (counted in our transparency report), and one inmate who was released from our custody after the test was taken but before the results were back. That inmate stayed with us for a total of 4 days, and was in quarantine the entire time during her stay. All RIDOH protocols are being followed related to both the Officer and the former inmate. We wish them a speedy recovery.

Thank you and stay safe.
